Genitalia.
Segments VIII–XI forming a moderately elongate (L/W = 4.0) ovipositor (
Fig. 66a
). Sternum VIII with long, strap-like basal apodeme with apical end widened, a small membranous area in the center. Segment IX covered with minute setae; hemisternites with long basal rods, well sclerotized apically; baculum distinct, apical, shorter than gonocoxae; gonocoxae longer than broad. Spermatheca (
Fig. 66b
) with receptacle short, cone-shaped, slightly narrower at base than pump.
